#Approach:

Approach (Hinglish) – Single Element in Sorted Array

Array sorted hai aur har element 2 baar aata hai except ek element jo sirf 1 baar aata hai.
Hume O(log n) time chahiye, isliye Binary Search use karenge.

Key Observation:
Normal pairs ka pattern:
First element even index par hota hai, second element odd index par hota hai.
Example: [1,1,2,2,3,3,4,4]
Pairs: (0,1), (2,3), (4,5), (6,7)

Lekin jab single element aata hai, uske baad pattern shift ho jata hai:
Single element ke left side -> (even, odd)
Single element ke right side -> (odd, even)

Steps:
1. Edge cases check karo:
   - Agar n == 1 -> return nums[0]
   - Agar first element single hai -> return nums[0]
   - Agar last element single hai -> return nums[n-1]

2. Binary search lagao:
   low = 1, high = n-2

3. mid calculate karo:
   mid = (low + high) / 2

4. Check karo mid single hai kya:
   Agar nums[mid] != nums[mid-1] AND nums[mid] != nums[mid+1]
   -> nums[mid] hi answer hai

5. Decide karo left ya right:
   Agar (mid even AND nums[mid] == nums[mid+1])
   OR (mid odd AND nums[mid] == nums[mid-1])
   -> Single element right side mein hai -> low = mid + 1
   Else
   -> Single element left side mein hai -> high = mid - 1

Time Complexity: O(log n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

One line intuition:
Single element ke baad pair indexing pattern shift ho jata hai,
us shift ko use karke binary search se answer find karte hain.

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int singleNonDuplicate(int[] nums) {
        int n = nums.length;
        if(n == 1) return nums[0];
        if(nums[0] != nums[1]){
            return nums[0];
        }
        if(nums[n-1] != nums[n-2]){
            return nums[n-1];
        }
        int low = 1;
        int high = n-2;

        while(low <= high){
            int mid = (low + high)/2;

            //CHeck if mid is the single element
            if(nums[mid] != nums[mid-1] && nums[mid] != nums[mid+1]){
                return nums[mid];
            }

            // if the element is in right then: (even,odd) -> element on right half
            // (odd,even) -> element on left half

            // for the condition if the element is in the right half
            else if((mid % 2 == 0 && nums[mid+1] == nums[mid]) || (mid % 2 == 1 && nums[mid-1] == nums[mid])){
                low = mid+1;
            }
            else{
                high = mid-1;
            }
        }
        return 1;
    }
}
